1
00:00:18,785 --> 00:00:20,419
In 2026, I, Kosei Neo,

2
00:00:20,420 --> 00:00:23,822
president of NEOXIS,

3
00:00:23,823 --> 00:00:27,827
should have died when someone pushed me…

4
00:00:28,395 --> 00:00:31,530
I ended up in the body of Eito Nomoto,
who looked just like me

5
00:00:31,531 --> 00:00:34,033
and was supposed to have died

6
00:00:34,034 --> 00:00:36,770
in an accident in 2012.
He was the son of Eiji Nomoto,

7
00:00:37,270 --> 00:00:39,272
the man caught in my fall.

8
00:00:41,007 --> 00:00:42,307
A decoy?

9
00:00:42,308 --> 00:00:45,678
<i>We'd like you to play
the role of President Neo.</i>

10
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:57,322
I'm already Kosei Neo, though…

11
00:00:57,323 --> 00:00:59,458
But I'll sell you that land.

12
00:00:59,459 --> 00:01:01,995
I can trust you as a business partner.

13
00:01:06,866 --> 00:01:09,635
Standing in for the Kosei Neo
of this timeline,

14
00:01:09,636 --> 00:01:12,171
I secured the office building site.

15
00:01:12,172 --> 00:01:14,173
That accident may have awakened

16
00:01:14,174 --> 00:01:16,708
a special ability in him.

17
00:01:16,709 --> 00:01:19,946
We have been fortunate
to encounter that talent.

18
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:23,016
Now it's a matter
of how we make use of it.

19
00:01:23,716 --> 00:01:27,053
For some reason, I found myself
wishing this moment would last forever.

20
00:01:36,262 --> 00:01:39,399
And just as in my past life,

21
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:42,435
NEOXIS's new headquarters was completed.

22
00:01:45,071 --> 00:01:46,506
<i>In the previous history, this was</i>

23
00:01:47,307 --> 00:01:50,443
<i>when Kosei Neo's isolation began to
deepen, leading to a series of tragedies.</i>

24
00:02:02,122 --> 00:02:04,491
If I live on as Eito,

25
00:02:05,692 --> 00:02:07,060
what will become

26
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:09,395
of that future?

27
00:02:21,107 --> 00:02:21,941
‎Eito!

28
00:02:22,642 --> 00:02:23,609
‎Eito!

29
00:02:23,610 --> 00:02:25,445
- <i>After collapsing at the festival…</i>
- Eito!

30
00:02:26,479 --> 00:02:29,382
…I had been under observation
for headaches and dizziness…

31
00:02:32,385 --> 00:02:34,721
and was finishing my final hospital stay.

32
00:02:42,195 --> 00:02:43,563
You're awake?

33
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:46,366
How do you feel?

34
00:02:47,367 --> 00:02:48,201
I'm fine.

35
00:02:49,035 --> 00:02:50,369
Thank goodness.

36
00:02:50,370 --> 00:02:53,406
The doctor said there's
nothing wrong with your brain.

37
00:02:55,508 --> 00:02:56,743
You okay?

38
00:02:57,977 --> 00:02:58,811
Yeah.

39
00:03:04,217 --> 00:03:07,553
Get in now on next year's
Tokyo Olympics partnership?

40
00:03:07,554 --> 00:03:11,290
Knock Soman out of the top spot
and put NEOXIS there instead?

41
00:03:11,291 --> 00:03:15,127
And on top of that, we're acquiring a bank
only seven years after we were founded?

42
00:03:15,128 --> 00:03:16,796
That's exactly why I promoted

43
00:03:17,297 --> 00:03:19,365
all of you to the board.

44
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:22,602
Make it happen

45
00:03:23,403 --> 00:03:24,703
or quit.

46
00:03:24,704 --> 00:03:27,907
Which sounds more fun? Choose.

47
00:03:29,409 --> 00:03:30,243
Now we're talking.

48
00:03:30,810 --> 00:03:31,811
This is a fight worth having.

49
00:03:33,146 --> 00:03:36,748
However, there are significant hurdles
before a final decision can be made.

50
00:03:36,749 --> 00:03:38,283
Tomono,

51
00:03:38,284 --> 00:03:41,788
making that happen is your job.

52
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:44,791
Understood.

53
00:03:46,025 --> 00:03:49,395
If you push people too hard,
they'll end up resenting you.

54
00:03:50,129 --> 00:03:53,199
Maybe having a family
would mellow you out a little.

55
00:03:54,133 --> 00:03:56,469
I don't have good memories
when it comes to family.

56
00:03:57,036 --> 00:03:59,172
I'm sorry. I said something out of line.

57
00:04:00,740 --> 00:04:03,275
This is a gift from one of our clients.

58
00:04:03,276 --> 00:04:06,012
Eri, I think I've mentioned this before,

59
00:04:06,512 --> 00:04:08,481
- but just throw that kind of thing away.
- Huh?

60
00:04:08,982 --> 00:04:11,451
- Throw it away?
- Look,

61
00:04:11,951 --> 00:04:15,788
I have no way of knowing
what anyone thinks of me or their motives.

62
00:04:17,423 --> 00:04:20,158
Then can I take it home?

63
00:04:20,159 --> 00:04:22,161
I've warned you.

64
00:04:22,662 --> 00:04:24,396
If you’re okay with that, go ahead.

65
00:04:24,397 --> 00:04:25,798
Yes!

66
00:04:29,736 --> 00:04:31,236
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

67
00:04:31,237 --> 00:04:35,541
Then let's toast to the end
of Eito’s follow-up observation!

68
00:04:36,042 --> 00:04:40,913
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

69
00:04:42,081 --> 00:04:43,048
This is great!

70
00:04:43,049 --> 00:04:46,018
This is quite a spread, isn't it?

71
00:04:46,019 --> 00:04:49,187
They're all gifts from President Neo!

72
00:04:49,188 --> 00:04:52,557
Hey, you're eating
only the expensive stuff!

73
00:04:52,558 --> 00:04:54,960
But they're so good!

74
00:04:54,961 --> 00:04:57,329
That's my sea urchin and crab!

75
00:04:57,330 --> 00:04:59,364
- What?
- You idiot!

76
00:04:59,365 --> 00:05:01,733
- I had my eye on that crab!
- Wait!

77
00:05:01,734 --> 00:05:03,169
Then, I'll take this. Thanks!

78
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:06,672
Don't take the abalone too!

79
00:05:06,673 --> 00:05:07,973
- Thanks!
- I'll cut it.

80
00:05:07,974 --> 00:05:09,274
- After we cut it…
- Thanks.

81
00:05:09,275 --> 00:05:11,243
- Make it equal parts. Enough for everyone.
- For everyone…

82
00:05:11,244 --> 00:05:12,678
So, shall we go with an exacta?

83
00:05:12,679 --> 00:05:14,379
Yeah. One bet, all-in.

84
00:05:14,380 --> 00:05:16,548
- Oh, horse racing?
- Yeah.

85
00:05:16,549 --> 00:05:20,485
Hit one big win, and we'll really
celebrate Eito's discharge in style.

86
00:05:20,486 --> 00:05:22,554
Gets my blood pumping.

87
00:05:22,555 --> 00:05:24,289
- Maybe I'll join in.
- Oh!

88
00:05:24,290 --> 00:05:26,158
- Nice.
- You can't, Kinpei.

89
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:28,427
A man who frequents Ginza

90
00:05:28,428 --> 00:05:31,530
builds wealth through investment,
then buys horses and becomes an owner.

91
00:05:31,531 --> 00:05:34,200
Ginza? Dad, you're still…

92
00:05:34,701 --> 00:05:37,836
- It's educational, I'm telling you.
- Right.

93
00:05:37,837 --> 00:05:40,706
- And beautiful women too.
- Yeah.

94
00:05:40,707 --> 00:05:44,042
You can hear all kinds of useful things
for the shopping street's future.

95
00:05:44,043 --> 00:05:48,081
They all smell so nice too.

96
00:05:56,456 --> 00:06:01,193
Well, they've both lost their wives,
so let's go easy on them.

97
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:04,029
And hey, introduce me to a good man
if you find one.

98
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:07,266
- What?
- What are you saying?

99
00:06:10,536 --> 00:06:12,472
That's amazing, Eito!

100
00:06:13,106 --> 00:06:14,406
It came off!

101
00:06:14,407 --> 00:06:17,008
- Hey, Kinpei!
- It was Kinpei!

102
00:06:17,009 --> 00:06:19,245
He looks well!

103
00:06:20,580 --> 00:06:22,848
Everyone looks so happy.

104
00:06:22,849 --> 00:06:26,017
If your painting gets accepted
on top of this, it'll be perfect.

105
00:06:26,018 --> 00:06:29,589
But it's not an easy competition.

106
00:06:30,590 --> 00:06:33,326
It's a prestigious
international competition.

107
00:06:33,893 --> 00:06:35,528
Just entering is impressive.

108
00:06:36,028 --> 00:06:38,296
If I win,

109
00:06:38,297 --> 00:06:40,900
it might change my life.

110
00:06:42,168 --> 00:06:46,239
If I were a judge,
your painting would definitely win.

111
00:06:49,542 --> 00:06:51,843
Everyone gets one piece!

112
00:06:51,844 --> 00:06:55,782
<i>But I harbored a secret fear.</i>

113
00:06:57,417 --> 00:07:00,586
<i>In a sci-fi novel I read
during my observation,</i>

114
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:04,257
<i>a man who used
past-life memories to succeed</i>

115
00:07:04,757 --> 00:07:08,694
<i>eventually had to pay the price.</i>

116
00:07:09,362 --> 00:07:11,797
We'll use this amazing fried food
to draw people in,

117
00:07:11,798 --> 00:07:14,433
<i>revitalize the shopping street,
and take on the supermarket!</i>

118
00:07:14,434 --> 00:07:15,901
AKARI SHOPPING STREET

119
00:07:15,902 --> 00:07:17,270
FRUIT AND VEGETABLE SHOP

120
00:07:18,237 --> 00:07:20,705
<i>Let's all launch
a climate business together.</i>

121
00:07:20,706 --> 00:07:23,141
Let's all start a company.
The name will be

122
00:07:23,142 --> 00:07:25,710
<i>Akari Shopping Street Co., Ltd.</i>

123
00:07:25,711 --> 00:07:27,345
Perhaps

124
00:07:27,346 --> 00:07:30,817
<i>you have foresight,
the ability to predict the future.</i>

125
00:07:32,084 --> 00:07:34,754
<i>Will the day come
when I will have to pay the price?</i>

126
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:36,589
<i>In the novel,</i>

127
00:07:37,089 --> 00:07:40,927
<i>the price was one's life.</i>

128
00:07:43,262 --> 00:07:45,263
CHAPTER 10
SUCCESS AND ITS COST

129
00:07:45,264 --> 00:07:47,499
THOSE WHO CHANGED HISTORY AND ACHIEVED
SUCCESS WILL HAVE TO PAY THE PRICE

130
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:49,202
THE PRICE IS LIFE

131
00:07:52,738 --> 00:07:55,407
<i>An IT Strategy Council
has been established</i>

132
00:07:55,408 --> 00:07:58,444
<i>as a government advisory body,</i>

133
00:07:59,011 --> 00:08:03,783
<i>with Soman's
President Ichimanda as chairman.</i>

134
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:06,719
<i>Ichimanda emphasized at a press conference</i>

135
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:10,922
<i>that Japan's digitization,
which has fallen behind the rest</i>

136
00:08:10,923 --> 00:08:14,560
<i>of the world, would be accelerated
through a public-private partnership.</i>

137
00:08:34,413 --> 00:08:36,349
Tomono, what is it?

138
00:08:37,316 --> 00:08:41,454
<i>I'd like to move forward
with the matter I proposed.</i>

139
00:08:47,026 --> 00:08:48,728
President Neo wants to meet with me?

140
00:08:49,395 --> 00:08:52,064
He wants to formalize a contract with you.

141
00:08:52,565 --> 00:08:56,935
He'd like you as an advisor
on a future strategy project

142
00:08:56,936 --> 00:08:59,438
under his direct supervision,
to counter Soman.

143
00:09:01,607 --> 00:09:05,610
<i>The day I hire myself has finally come…</i>

144
00:09:05,611 --> 00:09:09,114
As the shopping street's representative,

145
00:09:09,115 --> 00:09:13,418
a closer relationship with NEOXIS,
which carries our products online,

146
00:09:13,419 --> 00:09:14,687
is reassuring.

147
00:09:15,621 --> 00:09:17,390
Thank you.

148
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:19,991
<i>More than that,</i>

149
00:09:19,992 --> 00:09:24,330
<i>if I could get close to Kosei Neo himself…</i>

150
00:09:24,830 --> 00:09:29,401
<i>I could prevent the eviction
that happened in my past timeline.</i>

151
00:09:29,402 --> 00:09:32,070
We will not sell…

152
00:09:32,071 --> 00:09:32,971
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

153
00:09:32,972 --> 00:09:34,140
…our hometown for money.

154
00:09:35,374 --> 00:09:36,976
<i>Perhaps that's why…</i>

155
00:09:39,779 --> 00:09:42,548
I came here.

156
00:10:06,639 --> 00:10:07,707
<i>The new building…</i>

157
00:10:08,474 --> 00:10:12,278
<i>had the same design
I created in my past life.</i>

158
00:10:20,152 --> 00:10:21,220
<i>I was filled</i>

159
00:10:21,854 --> 00:10:24,423
<i>with anticipation and anxiety
at the thought</i>

160
00:10:25,024 --> 00:10:26,025
<i>of meeting myself.</i>

161
00:10:28,728 --> 00:10:29,595
Please come in.

162
00:10:32,698 --> 00:10:34,433
Huh? Where's the president?

163
00:10:35,167 --> 00:10:37,970
He's dealing with an urgent matter
and won't be here today.

164
00:10:38,938 --> 00:10:40,306
I see…

165
00:10:43,476 --> 00:10:44,710
Excuse us.

166
00:10:45,277 --> 00:10:47,145
Shall we begin, then?

167
00:10:47,146 --> 00:10:51,316
First, regarding
the Tokyo Olympics partnership.

168
00:10:51,317 --> 00:10:54,619
President Neo sees it as prime opportunity

169
00:10:54,620 --> 00:10:56,188
to promote NEOXIS to the world.

170
00:10:58,991 --> 00:11:00,493
<i>But I know better.</i>

171
00:11:01,594 --> 00:11:02,894
<i>The Olympics were postponed</i>

172
00:11:02,895 --> 00:11:05,898
<i>for a year due to COVID
and were held without spectators.</i>

173
00:11:07,066 --> 00:11:10,469
<i>NEOXIS suffered enormous losses.</i>

174
00:11:12,038 --> 00:11:14,707
Can we consider other ways
to promote ourselves besides the Olympics?

175
00:11:15,675 --> 00:11:16,941
Besides the Olympics?

176
00:11:16,942 --> 00:11:21,246
For example, supporting
overseas infectious disease efforts.

177
00:11:21,247 --> 00:11:25,984
For a company whose motto is
"For the People," that fits better.

178
00:11:25,985 --> 00:11:28,653
Are you telling us
to go against President Neo's orders?

179
00:11:28,654 --> 00:11:32,158
What if the Olympics venture
ends in failure?

180
00:11:32,758 --> 00:11:33,826
Huh?

181
00:11:34,460 --> 00:11:37,763
If the Olympics schedule is disrupted,

182
00:11:38,731 --> 00:11:40,700
it could mean enormous losses.

183
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:42,834
That would never happen!

184
00:11:42,835 --> 00:11:44,537
On what basis are you saying this?

185
00:11:47,940 --> 00:11:49,008
A hunch.

186
00:11:52,278 --> 00:11:53,512
A hunch?!

187
00:11:54,246 --> 00:11:55,780
That's completely absurd!

188
00:11:55,781 --> 00:11:58,317
If you care about NEOXIS's future,

189
00:11:58,818 --> 00:12:00,218
you should listen to me.

190
00:12:00,219 --> 00:12:01,587
This is pointless.

191
00:12:57,443 --> 00:13:00,678
- Brother? What are you doing here?
- Oh.

192
00:13:00,679 --> 00:13:02,347
Sarasa was here, so…

193
00:13:02,348 --> 00:13:05,383
She's meeting with President Neo
about a solo exhibition

194
00:13:05,384 --> 00:13:09,120
hosted by NEOXIS
and an art special on NEOXIS TV.

195
00:13:09,121 --> 00:13:10,856
It's his pet project.

196
00:13:11,423 --> 00:13:13,391
- His personal project?
- Yeah.

197
00:13:13,392 --> 00:13:15,094
Isn't he busy?

198
00:13:16,128 --> 00:13:18,097
I didn't hear anything from Sarasa.

199
00:13:21,066 --> 00:13:21,901
What?

200
00:13:25,204 --> 00:13:27,239
Oh, Sarasa! Where's the president?

201
00:13:28,073 --> 00:13:29,941
I managed to see him briefly,
but he was busy.

202
00:13:29,942 --> 00:13:31,076
Oh, I see…

203
00:13:36,282 --> 00:13:37,116
What's wrong?

204
00:13:37,850 --> 00:13:40,920
Seems like my brother is jealous.

205
00:13:49,361 --> 00:13:50,496
What?

206
00:13:51,063 --> 00:13:53,399
You really do look like President Neo.

207
00:13:53,966 --> 00:13:55,467
Oh, yeah…

208
00:13:59,138 --> 00:14:00,839
<i>Come to think of it,</i>

209
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:03,308
<i>Kosei Neo is me.</i>

210
00:14:03,309 --> 00:14:05,043
<i>So it's not strange</i>

211
00:14:05,044 --> 00:14:07,879
<i>that he might fall for Sarasa
the same way I did, is it?</i>

212
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:08,714
AKARI SHOPPING STREET

213
00:14:12,651 --> 00:14:15,487
<i>And it wouldn't be strange for Sarasa</i>

214
00:14:16,455 --> 00:14:19,358
<i>to develop feelings for Kosei Neo either.</i>

215
00:14:23,095 --> 00:14:25,297
Why didn't you tell me
about the exhibition and the special?

216
00:14:26,332 --> 00:14:28,801
I wanted to surprise you.

217
00:14:30,603 --> 00:14:31,804
That wasn't a lie?

218
00:14:34,340 --> 00:14:36,674
Were you really jealous?

219
00:14:36,675 --> 00:14:37,877
I was not.

220
00:14:39,378 --> 00:14:42,314
You weren't? How disappointing.

221
00:14:43,148 --> 00:14:44,817
I was.

222
00:14:45,751 --> 00:14:46,585
What?

223
00:14:47,686 --> 00:14:49,754
I followed you

224
00:14:49,755 --> 00:14:51,257
<i>and watched the two of you.</i>

225
00:15:04,169 --> 00:15:07,005
President Neo has ordered us to proceed
with the bank acquisition.

226
00:15:07,006 --> 00:15:10,008
Takarabe, our finance director,

227
00:15:10,009 --> 00:15:13,044
believes Vena Bank is the best candidate.

228
00:15:13,045 --> 00:15:17,283
Vena Holdings is open to a sale,
and their finances are extremely sound.

229
00:15:17,783 --> 00:15:21,320
If that's your assessment, Takarabe,
then Vena Bank seems right.

230
00:15:22,521 --> 00:15:25,324
Can we really trust
their sound management?

231
00:15:27,159 --> 00:15:29,228
They might be hiding negative equity.

232
00:15:29,795 --> 00:15:31,029
Do you have evidence of that?

233
00:15:31,030 --> 00:15:33,197
They may make troublesome demands.

234
00:15:33,198 --> 00:15:34,400
Demands?

235
00:15:35,267 --> 00:15:37,869
Like wanting
a large plot of land in the city.

236
00:15:37,870 --> 00:15:39,772
Then give us your basis for saying so!

237
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:43,542
<i>I know.</i>

238
00:15:44,610 --> 00:15:46,144
<i>Acquiring Vena Bank</i>

239
00:15:46,145 --> 00:15:49,214
<i>brought NEOXIS massive losses,</i>

240
00:15:49,915 --> 00:15:52,684
<i>and the sale conditions included a demand</i>

241
00:15:52,685 --> 00:15:55,753
<i>for a vast plot of land in the city,</i>

242
00:15:55,754 --> 00:15:58,023
<i>which led to the eviction
of the shopping street.</i>

243
00:15:58,590 --> 00:16:00,626
<i>That's the bitter memory
I carry from before.</i>

244
00:16:04,663 --> 00:16:05,531
A hunch.

245
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:12,136
Did you come here to obstruct us?

246
00:16:12,137 --> 00:16:14,072
As advisor,

247
00:16:14,073 --> 00:16:17,475
I recommend the second candidate,
Brother Bank.

248
00:16:17,476 --> 00:16:21,113
If you won't consider it,
there's no point in my being here.

249
00:16:22,381 --> 00:16:24,216
Then you don't need to be here.

250
00:16:24,883 --> 00:16:28,487
You may not be needed
at this company at all.

251
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:33,192
Tomono,

252
00:16:34,393 --> 00:16:36,027
can you arrange a chance

253
00:16:36,028 --> 00:16:39,431
for me to speak with President Neo?

254
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,002
I'll try.

255
00:16:46,138 --> 00:16:50,242
Well, you can't blame people
for not understanding

256
00:16:50,876 --> 00:16:53,512
the nature of Eito's abilities.

257
00:16:54,446 --> 00:16:58,150
Explaining those abilities
is no easy task either.

258
00:16:59,351 --> 00:17:01,285
Then why not investigate

259
00:17:01,286 --> 00:17:06,492
Brother Bank's situation
and use that to persuade them?

260
00:17:06,992 --> 00:17:10,062
I tried that, but all I found

261
00:17:10,796 --> 00:17:12,531
was negative information about them.

262
00:17:13,098 --> 00:17:17,503
But this is the man
who foresaw Trump's victory.

263
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:23,308
I can no longer resist
his ability to see what's coming.

264
00:17:32,051 --> 00:17:33,751
Why?

265
00:17:33,752 --> 00:17:38,223
President Neo wanted to hire me.
Surely, he can spare a moment to talk.

266
00:17:39,024 --> 00:17:42,728
I'm sorry. He's occupied
with pressing matters.

267
00:17:43,395 --> 00:17:44,395
Got it.

268
00:17:44,396 --> 00:17:45,630
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

269
00:17:45,631 --> 00:17:46,665
See you.

270
00:17:48,767 --> 00:17:51,970
If he has time to see Sarasa,
why can't he see me?

271
00:17:53,439 --> 00:17:56,307
- Brother! Come, quick!
- What?

272
00:17:56,308 --> 00:17:58,343
- Hurry!
- Huh?

273
00:18:01,380 --> 00:18:02,848
Sarasa!

274
00:18:04,483 --> 00:18:07,318
At the Lumière International
Painting Competition…

275
00:18:07,319 --> 00:18:08,387
Don't tell me? She won?

276
00:18:09,455 --> 00:18:12,090
She won the gold award! The top prize!

277
00:18:12,091 --> 00:18:13,292
Huh?

278
00:18:13,892 --> 00:18:15,594
You did it, Sarasa!

279
00:18:16,528 --> 00:18:17,629
Kinpei!

280
00:18:18,730 --> 00:18:21,166
Dad! I got an award!

281
00:18:24,703 --> 00:18:25,771
Dad…

282
00:18:34,446 --> 00:18:37,149
You're amazing, Sarasa!

283
00:18:38,917 --> 00:18:41,153
Recognized by the whole world!

284
00:18:42,621 --> 00:18:43,555
That's incredible!

285
00:18:46,792 --> 00:18:48,327
One, two!

286
00:18:48,961 --> 00:18:50,728
CONGRATS! SARASA IKETANI
GOLD AWARD

287
00:18:50,729 --> 00:18:53,631
Congratulations, Sarasa!

288
00:18:53,632 --> 00:18:58,237
The Akari Shopping Street has its heroine!

289
00:19:03,809 --> 00:19:06,811
Isn't that great, Kinpei? Hey!

290
00:19:06,812 --> 00:19:09,547
Come on!

291
00:19:09,548 --> 00:19:12,351
Iketani, would you say a few words?

292
00:19:12,851 --> 00:19:17,155
This award isn't mine alone.

293
00:19:17,156 --> 00:19:21,860
Someone gave me the push I needed
when I was about to give up.

294
00:19:25,964 --> 00:19:29,200
This award has opened up my world.

295
00:19:29,201 --> 00:19:32,103
It won't be an easy path,

296
00:19:32,104 --> 00:19:35,574
but I've made up my mind
to live as a painter.

297
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:39,945
<i>That should have been</i>

298
00:19:40,646 --> 00:19:44,015
<i>the best outcome I could have hoped for.</i>

299
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:45,249
LUMIÈRE INTERNATIONAL PAINTING COMPETITION
GOLD AWARD

300
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:46,451
CONGRATULATIONS
SARASA IKETANI

301
00:20:11,910 --> 00:20:15,247
Brother. It looks like
she's getting a commercial.

302
00:20:15,847 --> 00:20:16,815
A commercial?

303
00:20:17,583 --> 00:20:21,253
Sarasa is going to be
the face of NEOXIS's advertising.

304
00:20:23,855 --> 00:20:25,857
That doesn't make sense.

305
00:20:26,491 --> 00:20:27,391
What?

306
00:20:27,392 --> 00:20:30,595
Why is President Neo
going this far for her?

307
00:20:30,596 --> 00:20:33,665
It looks like he's putting
Sarasa ahead of the company's future.

308
00:20:35,300 --> 00:20:38,170
Doesn't that make you wonder about things?

309
00:20:40,439 --> 00:20:42,541
Wonder what exactly?

310
00:20:44,409 --> 00:20:47,145
- Nothing. I didn't mean it like that.
- Yes, you did.

311
00:20:52,751 --> 00:20:55,953
But why did Sarasa Iketani
even win that award?

312
00:20:55,954 --> 00:20:58,789
That prize is rumored
to have been bought before…

313
00:20:58,790 --> 00:21:01,759
Maybe she had a rich sponsor?

314
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,462
She'd make quite the mistress.

315
00:21:04,329 --> 00:21:05,297
Seriously?

316
00:21:06,064 --> 00:21:07,733
Don't spread garbage rumors.

317
00:21:08,233 --> 00:21:10,502
Sarasa Iketani won on her own merit.

318
00:21:11,270 --> 00:21:12,237
Sorry.

319
00:21:14,973 --> 00:21:17,476
Thank you. Please face this way.

320
00:21:19,244 --> 00:21:20,779
Please also face this way.

321
00:21:22,047 --> 00:21:24,683
- Thank you.
- Please also face this way.

322
00:21:30,022 --> 00:21:31,089
<i>I felt like</i>

323
00:21:32,391 --> 00:21:35,527
<i>Sarasa was drifting further
and further away from me.</i>

324
00:21:42,567 --> 00:21:43,668
Hey!

325
00:21:43,669 --> 00:21:44,568
Eito!

326
00:21:44,569 --> 00:21:46,772
Sorry for the sudden request to meet.

327
00:21:49,074 --> 00:21:50,809
Tomono told me.

328
00:21:51,710 --> 00:21:53,478
Sounds like things are tough.

329
00:22:03,689 --> 00:22:04,923
Let me introduce you to someone.

330
00:22:05,724 --> 00:22:08,460
President Ichimanda from Soman.

331
00:22:09,294 --> 00:22:10,795
<i>That's right.</i>

332
00:22:10,796 --> 00:22:14,999
<i>Even in my past timeline, Togo praised
Kosei Neo while cultivating ties</i>

333
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:18,637
<i>with President Ichimanda at the same time.</i>

334
00:22:19,137 --> 00:22:21,940
It's been a while.
I'm Ichimanda from Soman.

335
00:22:22,708 --> 00:22:26,977
You're not saying
we'd let Soman swallow us up?

336
00:22:26,978 --> 00:22:29,648
That's one option on the table.

337
00:22:30,782 --> 00:22:33,751
<i>With Soman even more successful now,</i>

338
00:22:33,752 --> 00:22:35,954
<i>he'd deepen that relationship further.</i>

339
00:22:36,455 --> 00:22:40,391
<i>Consulting Togo might be dangerous.</i>

340
00:22:40,392 --> 00:22:44,096
This is Eito Nomoto
of the Akari Shopping Street.

341
00:22:47,232 --> 00:22:49,401
He does look like Neo.

342
00:22:50,502 --> 00:22:52,971
- Good to meet you.
- Same here.

343
00:22:54,106 --> 00:22:58,043
I thought you might benefit
from Ichimanda's advice as well.

344
00:22:59,277 --> 00:23:00,177
Advice?

345
00:23:00,178 --> 00:23:02,013
Ichimanda says

346
00:23:02,514 --> 00:23:05,016
he wants to repay a debt to Neo.

347
00:23:06,084 --> 00:23:07,052
Repay a debt?

348
00:23:08,286 --> 00:23:10,688
You see, Neo once told me I had taken

349
00:23:10,689 --> 00:23:15,060
<i>his father's building from him.</i>

350
00:23:15,861 --> 00:23:17,862
I thought it was a baseless accusation,

351
00:23:17,863 --> 00:23:22,134
<i>but while reviewing my real estate records
last month, I learned it was true.</i>

352
00:23:23,835 --> 00:23:25,503
I also learned that it caused Neo

353
00:23:25,504 --> 00:23:29,708
<i>to have a very difficult childhood.</i>

354
00:23:31,443 --> 00:23:33,577
I deeply regret it.

355
00:23:33,578 --> 00:23:34,779
<i>Huh?</i>

356
00:23:34,780 --> 00:23:36,515
As an apology,

357
00:23:37,015 --> 00:23:39,618
I want to devote myself
to NEOXIS's growth.

358
00:23:40,318 --> 00:23:41,153
<i>What?</i>

359
00:23:42,287 --> 00:23:43,954
Ichimanda has been involved for years

360
00:23:43,955 --> 00:23:47,391
in relief work for impoverished children.

361
00:23:47,392 --> 00:23:49,827
<i>Huh? What?</i>

362
00:23:49,828 --> 00:23:54,166
It aligns with Neo's
"For the People" philosophy.

363
00:23:55,133 --> 00:23:57,636
I also owe an apology
for the terrible things

364
00:23:58,203 --> 00:24:02,474
done to your shopping street
to protect my semiconductor business.

365
00:24:05,844 --> 00:24:08,980
Going forward, I'll spare no effort
in supporting the Akari Shopping Street.

366
00:24:09,981 --> 00:24:10,849
<i>Huh?</i>

367
00:24:13,051 --> 00:24:15,053
The Soman Arakawa superstore…

368
00:24:16,521 --> 00:24:17,789
will pull out.

369
00:24:18,723 --> 00:24:20,725
<i>Is he too good to be true?</i>

370
00:24:21,393 --> 00:24:25,797
I intend to introduce NEOXIS
to the Olympics partnership track.

371
00:24:26,598 --> 00:24:27,832
‎That’s a problem.

372
00:24:27,833 --> 00:24:30,735
I'd also like to lend my support
to the Vena Bank acquisition.

373
00:24:31,937 --> 00:24:34,573
Oh… please push for Brother Bank instead.

374
00:24:35,373 --> 00:24:36,341
Why do you think that?

375
00:24:38,844 --> 00:24:40,078
A hunch.

376
00:24:42,514 --> 00:24:44,449
There it is.

377
00:24:47,219 --> 00:24:50,855
Won’t you show me this so-called power

378
00:24:50,856 --> 00:24:52,456
to see the future as well?

379
00:24:52,457 --> 00:24:53,525
No…

380
00:24:54,125 --> 00:24:55,727
It's not something I can just show you…

381
00:24:56,394 --> 00:24:57,462
Oh, right.

382
00:24:58,196 --> 00:25:01,299
Both Ichimanda and I own horses.

383
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:04,169
We're running in the same race
this weekend.

384
00:25:05,003 --> 00:25:07,939
Can you foresee

385
00:25:08,440 --> 00:25:09,707
the result?

386
00:25:09,708 --> 00:25:12,911
No… Horse racing?

387
00:25:13,778 --> 00:25:15,946
<i>I'm truly very sorry.</i>

388
00:25:15,947 --> 00:25:19,284
I will make it up to you.

389
00:25:22,554 --> 00:25:23,855
What was that about?

390
00:25:24,589 --> 00:25:27,459
It's about horse racing.

391
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:29,827
Horse racing?

392
00:25:29,828 --> 00:25:33,397
At last week's big race,
Togo's horse came first,

393
00:25:33,398 --> 00:25:36,233
and Ichimanda's came second.
Did you know that?

394
00:25:36,234 --> 00:25:38,036
No, I didn't.

395
00:25:38,537 --> 00:25:43,974
It seems he had bet on Togo's horse
and the third-place finisher.

396
00:25:43,975 --> 00:25:47,444
Apparently, the odds
would have been enormous if it had hit.

397
00:25:47,445 --> 00:25:50,047
He's still quite bitter about it.

398
00:25:50,048 --> 00:25:52,284
He said he missed out on a huge payout.

399
00:25:53,919 --> 00:25:55,286
<i>I think it was the spring of 2019</i>

400
00:25:55,287 --> 00:26:00,659
<i>when NEOXIS TV launched
its horse racing program.</i>

401
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:03,360
<i>That's it.</i>

402
00:26:03,361 --> 00:26:05,797
Those two horses
should have finished first and second.

403
00:26:06,965 --> 00:26:08,232
Really?

404
00:26:08,233 --> 00:26:10,335
Now that's something to look forward to.

405
00:26:16,074 --> 00:26:18,976
AKARI-NU

406
00:26:18,977 --> 00:26:20,811
HORSE RACING NEWSPAPER

407
00:26:20,812 --> 00:26:23,515
TEN THOUSAND
TOGO KING

408
00:26:30,355 --> 00:26:33,257
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

409
00:26:33,258 --> 00:26:34,793
The idiots found me…

410
00:26:36,661 --> 00:26:39,363
Huh? Eito, are you betting on horses?

411
00:26:39,364 --> 00:26:42,000
Let's have a prediction battle
for old times' sake!

412
00:26:42,500 --> 00:26:44,502
- Let's go!
- I'm in!

413
00:26:45,036 --> 00:26:46,270
Your pride…

414
00:26:46,271 --> 00:26:49,206
There's a long shot here.

415
00:26:49,207 --> 00:26:51,276
Put in 100,000 yen,
and you'd get 10 million yen.

416
00:26:51,776 --> 00:26:55,245
A 4-6 exacta at 200-to-1.

417
00:26:55,246 --> 00:26:57,548
- 50,000 yen becomes 10 million yen?
- Right.

418
00:26:57,549 --> 00:26:59,183
You shouldn't.

419
00:26:59,184 --> 00:27:00,151
- Huh?
- What?

420
00:27:00,952 --> 00:27:04,955
You're all chasing long shots.
Romantic, but it won't happen.

421
00:27:04,956 --> 00:27:07,024
How can you be so sure?

422
00:27:07,025 --> 00:27:08,159
No…

423
00:27:08,860 --> 00:27:12,364
Come to think of it, didn't Eri's company
just start a horse racing show?

424
00:27:12,931 --> 00:27:14,665
Do you have some inside information?

425
00:27:14,666 --> 00:27:17,235
There's no insider information
in horse racing.

426
00:27:18,436 --> 00:27:20,804
So what are you betting on?

427
00:27:20,805 --> 00:27:21,840
Show us!

428
00:27:22,741 --> 00:27:25,309
Togo King and Ten Thousand?

429
00:27:25,310 --> 00:27:26,977
Going for a medium long shot?

430
00:27:26,978 --> 00:27:30,881
An exacta on these two at 50-to-1
would be good odds.

431
00:27:30,882 --> 00:27:33,384
Put in 200,000 yen
and that's 10 million yen.

432
00:27:33,385 --> 00:27:36,320
10 million yen? Why are you
so fixated on 10 million yen?

433
00:27:36,321 --> 00:27:37,621
- Huh?
- Huh?

434
00:27:37,622 --> 00:27:38,890
You don't know, Eito?

435
00:27:39,457 --> 00:27:42,660
Maybe I should just close my shop.

436
00:27:42,661 --> 00:27:46,730
What are you saying, Hideko?
That's absolutely not an option!

437
00:27:46,731 --> 00:27:49,933
Your croquettes and minced cutlets
are what make this shopping street thrive.

438
00:27:49,934 --> 00:27:52,603
- What?
- But if something like this

439
00:27:52,604 --> 00:27:54,071
gets posted online…

440
00:27:54,072 --> 00:27:56,573
It's all a false accusation!

441
00:27:56,574 --> 00:27:57,475
What?

442
00:27:59,077 --> 00:27:59,911
Huh?

443
00:28:00,912 --> 00:28:02,413
A food poisoning diagnosis form?

444
00:28:02,414 --> 00:28:03,881
DIAGNOSIS REPORT
FOOD POISONING FROM CROQUETTE

445
00:28:03,882 --> 00:28:06,317
And photo of an insect in the croquette.

446
00:28:06,818 --> 00:28:10,888
You can easily doctor a photo like that.

447
00:28:10,889 --> 00:28:12,257
How did it come to this?

448
00:28:12,757 --> 00:28:15,659
A rude customer showed up at the shop.

449
00:28:15,660 --> 00:28:19,563
- Akari croquettes and Akari cutlets.
- Thank you!

450
00:28:19,564 --> 00:28:21,999
Thank you! Thanks for waiting!

451
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,501
One Akari cutlet, please!

452
00:28:24,302 --> 00:28:26,270
- Cutting in line--
- One Akari cutlet, please!

453
00:28:26,271 --> 00:28:28,405
Everyone's waiting their turn!

454
00:28:28,406 --> 00:28:30,208
But I'm a customer too!

455
00:28:30,909 --> 00:28:32,943
You call yourself a customer?

456
00:28:32,944 --> 00:28:35,946
If you can't follow the rules, get out!

457
00:28:35,947 --> 00:28:37,181
Don't ever come back!

458
00:28:37,182 --> 00:28:40,485
I'll come back again.
Maybe I'll flame you online!

459
00:28:41,119 --> 00:28:42,854
Maybe I went a bit too far.

460
00:28:43,421 --> 00:28:44,956
And this is his revenge?

461
00:28:45,724 --> 00:28:47,759
I went to confront him and ended up

462
00:28:48,593 --> 00:28:49,493
getting beaten up.

463
00:28:49,494 --> 00:28:50,662
Hey!

464
00:28:51,996 --> 00:28:52,831
Sorry!

465
00:28:55,467 --> 00:28:57,401
He punched me too.

466
00:28:57,402 --> 00:29:01,306
If he used violence, that gives us
something to hold over him, right?

467
00:29:01,906 --> 00:29:04,509
Kinpei threw the first punch, though.

468
00:29:05,276 --> 00:29:08,245
Now he's demanding an enormous settlement.

469
00:29:08,246 --> 00:29:11,148
Who can pay 10 million yen?!

470
00:29:11,149 --> 00:29:12,750
<i>10 million yen again.</i>

471
00:29:12,751 --> 00:29:14,985
If this lie gets out,

472
00:29:14,986 --> 00:29:17,689
what's going to happen to us
and the shopping street?

473
00:29:19,324 --> 00:29:20,425
I'm sorry,

474
00:29:21,292 --> 00:29:22,860
Eito.

475
00:29:22,861 --> 00:29:26,598
You helped us thrive, and now this.

476
00:29:28,867 --> 00:29:29,934
For now,

477
00:29:30,735 --> 00:29:31,736
let's get 10 million yen together.

478
00:29:32,537 --> 00:29:33,371
- Huh?
- What?

479
00:29:34,038 --> 00:29:35,506
From where?

480
00:29:35,507 --> 00:29:36,940
We'll win it at the Toka Stakes.

481
00:29:36,941 --> 00:29:38,008
Horse racing?

482
00:29:38,009 --> 00:29:40,210
You're that confident?!

483
00:29:40,211 --> 00:29:42,446
If Eito says so, I'm in.

484
00:29:42,447 --> 00:29:45,350
We'd need to put in 200,000 yen
to get 10 million back.

485
00:29:46,151 --> 00:29:47,484
Let's all chip in!

486
00:29:47,485 --> 00:29:48,418
Right.

487
00:29:48,419 --> 00:29:51,523
If we win,

488
00:29:52,023 --> 00:29:54,691
Eito will be the hero
of the Akari Shopping Street!

489
00:29:54,692 --> 00:29:56,760
That's right!

490
00:29:56,761 --> 00:29:57,961
<i>And once again,</i>

491
00:29:57,962 --> 00:30:00,465
<i>I'd be using my memories
from my past life.</i>

492
00:30:02,066 --> 00:30:03,134
<i>In the novel,</i>

493
00:30:03,635 --> 00:30:06,504
<i>the price was one's life.</i>

494
00:30:13,511 --> 00:30:15,013
If we win,

495
00:30:15,513 --> 00:30:18,282
- it will be our first win.
- Yes, mine too.

496
00:30:18,283 --> 00:30:20,118
- Excuse us.
- Huh?

497
00:30:23,421 --> 00:30:25,389
Who will take first?

498
00:30:25,390 --> 00:30:27,258
That's right.

499
00:30:27,759 --> 00:30:32,229
President Ichimanda is here…
What were you thinking, inviting him?

500
00:30:32,230 --> 00:30:33,565
Ichimanda says

501
00:30:34,432 --> 00:30:37,802
he wants to help
Akari Shopping Street and NEOXIS.

502
00:30:39,070 --> 00:30:39,904
What?

503
00:30:42,507 --> 00:30:44,609
This is a race we can't afford to lose.

504
00:30:47,045 --> 00:30:50,280
PREVIOUS LIFE IN 1991

505
00:30:50,281 --> 00:30:52,850
Come on!

506
00:30:52,851 --> 00:30:55,053
Here it is!

507
00:30:58,056 --> 00:30:59,691
Dammit!

508
00:31:01,526 --> 00:31:04,229
Did you lose, Papa?

509
00:31:06,097 --> 00:31:08,566
Papa's finished.

510
00:31:10,568 --> 00:31:14,205
Papa…

511
00:31:16,441 --> 00:31:20,578
Kosei, don't look down. Look up.

512
00:31:23,047 --> 00:31:24,916
Your father is going up there someday.

513
00:31:28,152 --> 00:31:30,355
You aim for the top too.

514
00:31:35,326 --> 00:31:37,128
What are you thinking about?

515
00:31:41,633 --> 00:31:42,967
Right now, I can see…

516
00:31:44,302 --> 00:31:46,371
two kinds of people.

517
00:31:51,476 --> 00:31:53,778
Those who look down from above,

518
00:31:55,079 --> 00:31:57,181
like Togo and Ichimanda…

519
00:31:58,149 --> 00:32:00,818
- Something this happy…
- Right…

520
00:32:05,924 --> 00:32:07,258
…and those

521
00:32:08,593 --> 00:32:10,595
who look up from below.

522
00:32:16,734 --> 00:32:18,336
Which kind

523
00:32:19,904 --> 00:32:21,105
is Kosei Neo?

524
00:32:26,177 --> 00:32:28,546
Neither.

525
00:32:29,647 --> 00:32:31,049
"For the People."

526
00:32:31,549 --> 00:32:35,420
He founded NEOXIS to save everyone.

527
00:32:41,426 --> 00:32:42,994
I hope that's still true.

528
00:32:49,267 --> 00:32:50,300
‎TOWA 11R-79TH TOKA STAKES

529
00:32:50,301 --> 00:32:52,269
<i>Burning Soul is in the gate.</i>

530
00:32:52,270 --> 00:32:56,040
<i>Blessing from Heaven is in the gate
and all ready to go.</i>

531
00:32:58,843 --> 00:33:00,911
- Togo King and Ten Thousand!
- <i>Who will win the crown?</i>

532
00:33:00,912 --> 00:33:01,878
Please!

533
00:33:01,879 --> 00:33:03,413
Save the shopping street!

534
00:33:03,414 --> 00:33:05,917
<i>We're off to a clean start
at the 79th Toka Stakes!</i>

535
00:33:06,684 --> 00:33:08,418
<i>A well-synchronized break from the gate!</i>

536
00:33:08,419 --> 00:33:11,588
<i>From the outside, No. 2 Togo King
is close to the lead.</i>

537
00:33:11,589 --> 00:33:15,092
- <i>Right behind, No. 1 Ten Thousand…</i>
- Good job, Togo King!

538
00:33:15,093 --> 00:33:17,795
- Come on, Ten Thousand!
- <i>No. 8 Daiichi Helios…</i>

539
00:33:18,963 --> 00:33:23,900
<i>Into the third turn, running neck and neck
No. 2 Togo King and No. 8 Daiichi Helios…</i>

540
00:33:23,901 --> 00:33:25,836
<i>The gap is closing,
under 400 meters to go.</i>

541
00:33:25,837 --> 00:33:29,773
<i>Challenging them is No. 7 Meguro Farmer,
with the jockey riding hard in third.</i>

542
00:33:29,774 --> 00:33:32,743
<i>In fourth is No. 1 Ten Thousand
by two and a half lengths.</i>

543
00:33:32,744 --> 00:33:34,745
<i>‎Continuing in fourth…</i>

544
00:33:34,746 --> 00:33:37,814
What are you doing, Ten Thousand!

545
00:33:37,815 --> 00:33:40,183
- Tired out?
- Let's go!

546
00:33:40,184 --> 00:33:42,853
<i>Onto the fourth turn and the home stretch!</i>

547
00:33:42,854 --> 00:33:44,621
- <i>No. 8 Daiichi Helios now takes the lead.</i>
- Hey!

548
00:33:44,622 --> 00:33:47,657
- Not yet!
- What are you doing?

549
00:33:47,658 --> 00:33:48,992
- Get it together!
- Togo King!

550
00:33:48,993 --> 00:33:50,994
- Let's go!
- <i>Togo King is holding on in second!</i>

551
00:33:50,995 --> 00:33:52,262
- Hey!
- <i>Swinging wide is No. 7 Meguro Farmer.</i>

552
00:33:52,263 --> 00:33:53,897
<i>On the inside is No. 1 Ten Thousand.</i>

553
00:33:53,898 --> 00:33:55,899
Go past them, Togo King!

554
00:33:55,900 --> 00:33:56,901
Here it is…

555
00:33:57,869 --> 00:33:58,869
Catch them!

556
00:33:58,870 --> 00:34:00,570
<i>Now from the outside
is No. 7 Meguro Farmer!</i>

557
00:34:00,571 --> 00:34:02,906
Come on! Come on, Togo King!

558
00:34:02,907 --> 00:34:04,608
Catch them, Ten Thousand!

559
00:34:04,609 --> 00:34:06,209
Come on!

560
00:34:06,210 --> 00:34:09,313
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

561
00:34:10,615 --> 00:34:12,482
Let's go!

562
00:34:12,483 --> 00:34:14,284
<i>Togo King and Ten Thousand
are falling behind!</i>

563
00:34:14,285 --> 00:34:16,453
- Go, Togo King!
- Ten Thousand!

564
00:34:16,454 --> 00:34:19,023
<i>Can Togo King and Ten Thousand fight back?</i>

565
00:34:21,492 --> 00:34:25,195
<i>But they can't make it!
No. 8 Daiichi Helios holds on to win!</i>

566
00:34:25,196 --> 00:34:27,465
- <i>Then Meguro Farmer…</i>
- What?

567
00:34:28,099 --> 00:34:29,967
They didn't come through!

568
00:34:30,902 --> 00:34:32,502
What's going to happen
to the shopping street?!

569
00:34:32,503 --> 00:34:33,403
<i>Togo King and Ten Thousand…</i>

570
00:34:33,404 --> 00:34:34,872
- What? Come on!
- <i>…finish in the placings!</i>

571
00:34:36,107 --> 00:34:41,379
<i>The 79th Toka Stakes…</i>

572
00:34:41,879 --> 00:34:43,981
Fourth and fifth place.

573
00:34:44,916 --> 00:34:47,518
This isn't what you promised, is it?

574
00:34:51,422 --> 00:34:54,459
So this is your ability to see the future?

575
00:34:56,527 --> 00:34:59,363
A valuable lesson today.

576
00:35:00,665 --> 00:35:04,135
One shouldn't put too much faith
in the unscientific.

577
00:35:06,070 --> 00:35:07,939
Lesson learned.

578
00:35:14,545 --> 00:35:16,113
We heard.

579
00:35:16,114 --> 00:35:18,683
Your so-called hunch was wrong, it seems.

580
00:35:19,484 --> 00:35:21,953
Even so, I still recommend Brother Bank.

581
00:35:22,653 --> 00:35:24,387
About that…

582
00:35:24,388 --> 00:35:28,024
Prosecutors are apparently investigating
Brother Bank for fraud

583
00:35:28,025 --> 00:35:30,194
and misappropriation of funds.

584
00:35:31,796 --> 00:35:34,699
Thank God we didn't follow your advice.

585
00:35:35,967 --> 00:35:38,169
Are you here to destroy this company?!

586
00:35:39,103 --> 00:35:41,772
I only want to do my job.

587
00:35:42,273 --> 00:35:44,876
Please let me meet President Neo.

588
00:35:45,610 --> 00:35:48,279
I'm sorry, but that won't be possible.

589
00:35:53,251 --> 00:35:56,220
It pains me to say this, but after hearing

590
00:35:56,721 --> 00:35:59,456
everything that's happened,

591
00:35:59,457 --> 00:36:02,126
he wants to terminate your contract.

592
00:36:07,298 --> 00:36:10,101
What do you mean you're busy, Togo?

593
00:36:11,202 --> 00:36:13,137
I'm already outside the restaurant…

594
00:36:17,608 --> 00:36:18,843
Understood.

595
00:36:19,844 --> 00:36:22,847
I'll contact you again later.

596
00:36:30,354 --> 00:36:32,489
Thank you for today.

597
00:36:32,490 --> 00:36:34,058
- I'm glad.
- Yes.

598
00:36:35,993 --> 00:36:37,828
- From this side…
- Oh.

599
00:37:07,291 --> 00:37:08,726
Where is he going?

600
00:37:16,267 --> 00:37:17,935
Thank you so much for today.

601
00:37:43,227 --> 00:37:44,528
What's the matter, Eito?

602
00:37:46,397 --> 00:37:48,399
Why were you with President Neo?

603
00:37:50,067 --> 00:37:52,036
He was helping me with something.

604
00:37:52,937 --> 00:37:54,071
With what?

605
00:37:55,473 --> 00:37:56,874
Was I not supposed to see him?

606
00:38:00,711 --> 00:38:01,946
It's okay.

607
00:38:02,446 --> 00:38:05,816
President Neo felt for Hideko's situation.

608
00:38:07,585 --> 00:38:10,988
NEOXIS's lawyers will handle it, he said.

609
00:38:12,556 --> 00:38:13,824
I see…

610
00:38:17,962 --> 00:38:18,829
Let's go.

611
00:38:21,832 --> 00:38:23,433
SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT
SWORN STATEMENT

612
00:38:23,434 --> 00:38:27,471
This is the settlement agreement
and sworn statement from the other party.

613
00:38:28,572 --> 00:38:32,009
- So everything has been resolved?
- Yes.

614
00:38:33,778 --> 00:38:34,778
I'm glad!

615
00:38:34,779 --> 00:38:36,479
Thank you so much!

616
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:39,115
Aren't you glad, Hideko?

617
00:38:39,116 --> 00:38:40,517
Thank you.

618
00:38:40,518 --> 00:38:43,353
Thank you, Sarasa. And you too, Eito.

619
00:38:43,354 --> 00:38:45,689
No. I struck out completely.

620
00:38:45,690 --> 00:38:49,592
No, it's the thought that counts.

621
00:38:49,593 --> 00:38:51,861
Feeling everyone's care…

622
00:38:51,862 --> 00:38:54,998
It made me so grateful
to live in this town.

623
00:38:54,999 --> 00:38:56,032
Thank you.

624
00:38:56,033 --> 00:38:58,269
The shopping street is safe now.

625
00:38:59,036 --> 00:39:01,072
Shall we have a drink to celebrate?

626
00:39:01,906 --> 00:39:03,640
Let's go!

627
00:39:03,641 --> 00:39:05,743
I had it ready!

628
00:39:07,912 --> 00:39:09,179
Get the glasses!

629
00:39:09,180 --> 00:39:10,981
Eito, do you have a minute?

630
00:39:11,482 --> 00:39:13,317
Where?

631
00:39:15,019 --> 00:39:16,320
Excuse me.

632
00:39:20,658 --> 00:39:24,794
President Neo
has officially decided to proceed

633
00:39:24,795 --> 00:39:28,366
with the Olympics partnership
and the Vena Bank acquisition.

634
00:39:33,671 --> 00:39:34,839
I see.

635
00:39:38,409 --> 00:39:40,444
May I ask…

636
00:39:42,113 --> 00:39:46,984
the real reason you've been
so adamant in your opposition?

637
00:39:54,392 --> 00:39:55,693
It's a hunch.

638
00:39:58,062 --> 00:40:01,064
Keeping us out of Paris
before the terrorist attack,

639
00:40:01,065 --> 00:40:04,468
foreseeing Trump's victory…
Those were hunches too?

640
00:40:07,104 --> 00:40:09,073
I can't explain it any other way.

641
00:40:11,776 --> 00:40:13,977
If something that baseless had gone wrong,

642
00:40:13,978 --> 00:40:17,080
the way the race did,

643
00:40:17,081 --> 00:40:19,984
NEOXIS would've suffered enormous losses.

644
00:40:22,987 --> 00:40:26,756
<i>With 200 meters left,
No. 8 Ten Thousand is in the lead.</i>

645
00:40:26,757 --> 00:40:29,826
<i>No. 3 Togo King is catching up
and in second place.</i>

646
00:40:29,827 --> 00:40:31,828
<i>Closing the gap…
Ten Thousand is trying to hold on!</i>

647
00:40:31,829 --> 00:40:35,432
<i>Ten Thousand is trying to hold on!
Both are neck and neck… Togo King wins!</i>

648
00:40:35,433 --> 00:40:39,102
- <i>First place is No. 3 Togo King.</i>
- Come on!

649
00:40:39,103 --> 00:40:41,504
- No way!
- No way!

650
00:40:41,505 --> 00:40:45,108
- What happened?
- It came in! In the Tenho Stakes!

651
00:40:45,109 --> 00:40:47,477
Togo King and Ten Thousand,
with a one-two finish!

652
00:40:47,478 --> 00:40:49,580
Why didn't we bet on it?!

653
00:40:51,248 --> 00:40:52,750
That was the race?!

654
00:40:54,652 --> 00:40:57,421
Our horses, first and second…

655
00:40:59,223 --> 00:41:00,858
So it came through after all…

656
00:41:02,393 --> 00:41:04,495
Perhaps it's too soon

657
00:41:05,629 --> 00:41:07,698
to write him off.

658
00:41:09,867 --> 00:41:13,570
The Vena Bank acquisition talks
are proceeding smoothly…

659
00:41:13,571 --> 00:41:16,207
- However…
- However?

660
00:41:17,675 --> 00:41:22,445
Vena Holdings, which aims
to expand in Tokyo,

661
00:41:22,446 --> 00:41:27,918
demanded a 95,000 sq. meter plot of land
in the city on top of the sale price.

662
00:41:28,419 --> 00:41:31,955
With the Olympics a year away,
Tokyo land prices are skyrocketing.

663
00:41:31,956 --> 00:41:34,825
The timing couldn't be worse.

664
00:41:38,896 --> 00:41:40,897
They might make troublesome demands.

665
00:41:40,898 --> 00:41:43,634
Like wanting
a large plot of land in the city.

666
00:41:56,747 --> 00:41:59,783
<i>Even if this timeline
has changed many things,</i>

667
00:42:00,351 --> 00:42:03,119
<i>will the most critical part,</i>

668
00:42:03,120 --> 00:42:04,655
<i>the eviction, remain unchanged?</i>

669
00:42:06,824 --> 00:42:07,658
<i>No.</i>

670
00:42:08,659 --> 00:42:10,560
<i>As Eito Nomoto, I reached out</i>

671
00:42:10,561 --> 00:42:13,196
<i>a hand to the shopping street.</i>

672
00:42:13,197 --> 00:42:14,031
AKARI SHOPPING STREET

673
00:42:14,732 --> 00:42:18,035
<i>Will that change this future too?</i>

674
00:42:19,904 --> 00:42:23,140
<i>When 2020 arrives…</i>

675
00:42:23,908 --> 00:42:26,677
<i>the global spread of COVID-19</i>

676
00:42:27,244 --> 00:42:29,112
<i>will bring
the shopping street's foot traffic</i>

677
00:42:29,113 --> 00:42:31,481
<i>to a complete standstill.</i>

678
00:42:31,482 --> 00:42:33,716
<i>It has been announced</i>

679
00:42:33,717 --> 00:42:37,420
<i>that due to COVID-19,</i>

680
00:42:37,421 --> 00:42:41,659
<i>the 2020 Tokyo Olympics
will be postponed to 2021.</i>

681
00:42:43,160 --> 00:42:46,363
<i>If the Olympics schedule is disrupted,</i>

682
00:42:46,931 --> 00:42:49,032
it could mean enormous losses.

683
00:42:49,033 --> 00:42:52,335
In seven years, an epidemic
will turn the whole world upside down.

684
00:42:52,336 --> 00:42:54,170
<i>Prime Minister Abe and President Bach…</i>

685
00:42:54,171 --> 00:42:56,140
So he really can

686
00:42:56,974 --> 00:42:59,075
see the future?

687
00:42:59,076 --> 00:43:03,080
TOKYO OLYMPICS POSTPONED FOR ONE YEAR
FIRST TIME IN HISTORY

688
00:43:16,460 --> 00:43:17,394
<i>The future…</i>

689
00:43:33,811 --> 00:43:37,314
Someone who changes
history to achieve success…

690
00:43:39,049 --> 00:43:42,152
will have to pay with their life.

691
00:44:08,679 --> 00:44:10,214
Changing the future…

692
00:44:16,086 --> 00:44:18,389
What am I trying to protect?

693
00:44:19,056 --> 00:44:19,689
‎NEXT PREVIEW
‎FINALLY, THE ERA OF COVID BEGINS

694
00:44:19,690 --> 00:44:22,325
‎With the state of emergency now declared,

695
00:44:22,326 --> 00:44:24,360
‎-<i>‎we have to overcome this!</i>
‎-I want you to meet…

696
00:44:24,361 --> 00:44:25,428
<i>‎Kosei Neo.</i>

697
00:44:25,429 --> 00:44:27,263
‎In order to protect Akari Shopping Street…

698
00:44:27,264 --> 00:44:29,533
‎I won't forgive President Neo.

699
00:44:30,267 --> 00:44:32,568
<i>‎Could it have been… Tomono?</i>

700
00:44:32,569 --> 00:44:33,369
‎THE TRUTH BEHIND THE MURDER
‎IS GRADUALLY BEING UNCOVERED

701
00:44:33,370 --> 00:44:34,070
‎THIS DRAMA IS FICTION

702
00:44:34,071 --> 00:44:35,039
Subtitle translation by: Ken Nishizaki
